---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Affiliate Disclosure"
  description="Read the Urban Harvest Lab affiliate disclosure and learn how the site handles commissions, recommendations, and editorial independence."
  canonicalPath="/affiliate-disclosure/"
>
  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container page-hero">
      <div class="page-hero__panel">
        <span class="eyebrow">Affiliate disclosure</span>
        <h1>How affiliate links are used on Urban Harvest Lab.</h1>
        <p>
          Some articles may include affiliate links. If you click one of those links and make a purchase, Urban Harvest
          Lab may earn a commission at no additional cost to you.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container info-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="eyebrow">Editorial independence</span>
        <h2>Recommendations should still fit the problem</h2>
        <p>
          Commissions do not change the underlying recommendation standard. Products should be suggested because they
          fit the use case, not because they exist in an affiliate catalog.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="eyebrow">Disclosure placement</span>
        <h2>How readers are informed</h2>
        <p>
          Articles that may include affiliate links should contain a clear disclosure near the top of the page so the
          context is visible before the recommendation section.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="eyebrow">Reader-first policy</span>
        <h2>Better to say “skip it” than force a product</h2>
        <p>
          If a simple setup, a cheaper tool, or no purchase at all is the better answer, that is the recommendation
          that should appear in the guide.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="eyebrow">Questions</span>
        <h2>Need clarification?</h2>
        <p>
          Use the contact page if you want to ask how a product recommendation was framed or whether a link is
          commercial in nature.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
